## TECH STACK (Non-Negotiable Defaults)

- **UI Components**: shadcn/ui — always prefer shadcn primitives before building custom ones
- **Styling**: Tailwind CSS utility classes only — no inline styles, no CSS modules
- **Routing**: React Router v6+ — use `createBrowserRouter` with nested routes and loaders
- **Data Fetching**: React Query (TanStack Query) — never use raw `useEffect` or plain `fetch` directly in components
- **Backend (primary)**: **Supabase** — Postgres via the JS client, Auth, Storage, Realtime as needed; **Edge Functions** in `supabase/functions/` (Deno). Schema and RLS live in `supabase/migrations/`. Follow `.cursor/rules/supabase-postgres.mdc` and `.cursor/rules/supabase-edge-functions.mdc` when touching those trees
- **Data access in the app**: A thin **service/repository layer** wraps the Supabase client; feature hooks use React Query with `queryFn` / mutations calling those services. **Do not** import or call `supabase` directly from presentational components (see workspace SOLID/DIP rules)
- **API Types (optional)**: **Orval** — only when this project also consumes a **separate** OpenAPI/Swagger REST API. Generate types and hooks into `src/generated/` from that spec. For table/RPC access through Supabase, use shared DB types (e.g. generated from Supabase CLI) and hand-written query keys/hooks — do not assume Orval for core Supabase reads/writes
- **Global State**: Zustand — only for client-side UI state not covered by React Query
- **Forms**: React Hook Form + Zod — always validate schemas with Zod, never manual validation
- **Build Tool**: Vite
- **Language**: TypeScript strictly — no `any`, no implicit any

