## ABSOLUTE IMPORTS

Always use absolute imports. Configure `@` as the `src/` alias in `vite.config.ts` and `tsconfig.json`.

```ts
// ✅ Do this
import { Button } from '@/components/ui/button'
import { useAuth } from '@/hooks/useAuth'

// ❌ Never this
import { Button } from '../../../components/ui/button'
```

---

## COMPONENTS

### Single Responsibility
A component should do one thing. If it's doing too many things, extract child components or hooks.

```tsx
// ❌ Too much in one component
function Dashboard() {
  const [users, setUsers] = useState([])
  useEffect(() => { fetchUsers().then(setUsers) }, [])
  return (
    <div>
      {users.map(u => (
        <div key={u.id}>
          <h2>{u.name}</h2>
          <span>{u.email}</span>
          <button onClick={() => deleteUser(u.id)}>Delete</button>
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>
  )
}

// ✅ Decomposed
function Dashboard() {
  const { data: users } = useUsers()
  return <UserList users={users} />
}
```

### No Nested Render Functions
Never define render functions inside a component. Extract them as separate components instead.

```tsx
// ❌ Nested render function
function Component() {
  function renderHeader() {
    return <header>...</header>
  }
  return <div>{renderHeader()}</div>
}

// ✅ Separate component
function Header() {
  return <header>...</header>
}

function Component() {
  return <div><Header /></div>
}
```

### Favour Composition Over Configuration
Prefer composable components with `children` over large `config` prop objects.

```tsx
// ❌ Configuration-heavy
<Card title="Hello" footer="Bye" icon="info" collapsible />

// ✅ Composable
<Card>
  <Card.Header><InfoIcon /> Hello</Card.Header>
  <Card.Body>...</Card.Body>
  <Card.Footer>Bye</Card.Footer>
</Card>
```

### Conditional Rendering
Keep JSX readable. Use ternaries for simple conditions; extract complex conditions to variables or components.

```tsx
// ✅ Simple condition
{isLoading ? <Spinner /> : <Content />}

// ✅ Complex: extract to variable
const content = isLoading
  ? <Spinner />
  : hasError
    ? <ErrorState />
    : <Content data={data} />

return <div>{content}</div>
```

### Use Descriptive Prop Names
Boolean props should read as adjectives or states, not verbs.

```tsx
// ❌
<Button show loading handleClick={onClick} />

// ✅
<Button visible isLoading onClick={onClick} />
```

### Destructure Props
Always destructure props at the function signature level.

```tsx
// ❌
function UserCard(props) {
  return <div>{props.user.name}</div>
}

// ✅
function UserCard({ user }: UserCardProps) {
  return <div>{user.name}</div>
}
```

### Component Size
If a component exceeds ~200 lines, it's probably doing too much. Break it apart.

