## STATE MANAGEMENT

### Choose the Right Tool

| Data type | Tool |
|---|---|
| Server / async data | React Query |
| Form data | React Hook Form |
| Global UI state (modals, theme) | Zustand |
| Local component state | `useState` / `useReducer` |
| Derived values | Compute inline, no extra state |

### Never Store Derived State

```tsx
// ❌ Derived state = bugs
const [fullName, setFullName] = useState(`${firstName} ${lastName}`)

// ✅ Compute it
const fullName = `${firstName} ${lastName}`
```

### Colocate State
Keep state as close to where it's used as possible. Only lift state when genuinely shared.

### Avoid useEffect for Data Fetching
Use React Query. Every raw `useEffect` for fetching is a bug waiting to happen (race conditions, missing cleanup, no caching).

```tsx
// ❌ Raw effect fetching
useEffect(() => {
  fetch('/api/users').then(r => r.json()).then(setUsers)
}, [])

// ✅ React Query — feature hook calling a service (Supabase or Orval-generated REST)
const { data: users, isLoading, error } = useUsers()
```

