## CUSTOM HOOKS

- Extract stateful logic into custom hooks to keep components clean
- A hook should do one thing
- Name hooks to describe what they return, not how they work: `useUserPermissions` not `useCheckAndFetchPermissions`
- Prefer hooks over HOCs and render props for composing behaviour

```ts
// ✅ Encapsulate complexity in a hook
function useDisclosure(defaultOpen = false) {
  const [isOpen, setIsOpen] = useState(defaultOpen)
  const open = useCallback(() => setIsOpen(true), [])
  const close = useCallback(() => setIsOpen(false), [])
  const toggle = useCallback(() => setIsOpen(v => !v), [])
  return { isOpen, open, close, toggle }
}
```

---

## TYPESCRIPT

- Always type component props with a named interface or type alias
- Never use `any` — use `unknown` and narrow the type if needed
- Use `as const` for literal value arrays/objects
- Prefer `interface` for object shapes, `type` for unions and mapped types
- Export types alongside their related components/hooks

```ts
interface UserCardProps {
  user: User
  onDelete: (id: string) => void
  isEditable?: boolean
}
```

---

## CODE STYLE

- Prefer `const` arrow functions for component definitions, or named `function` declarations — be consistent per file
- No dead code committed — remove unused imports, variables, commented-out blocks
- Keep imports ordered: external libs → internal absolute → relative
- Max one component per file (exceptions: tiny helper components used only within that file)
- Avoid magic numbers — extract to named constants

---

## WHAT TO AVOID

| ❌ Don't | ✅ Do instead |
|---|---|
| `useEffect` for data fetching | React Query |
| Plain `fetch` / `supabase` in components | Services + React Query hooks |
| Duplicated Supabase queries across features | One service function, reused query keys |
| Hand-writing types when Orval or Supabase codegen can supply them | Orval (OpenAPI) or `supabase gen types` for DB shapes |
| Manual form validation | Zod + React Hook Form |
| Relative import paths | Absolute `@/` paths |
| Nested render functions | Extract to components |
| `any` type | Proper types or `unknown` |
| Global CSS classes | Tailwind utilities |
| Storing derived state | Compute on the fly |
| Props drilling 3+ levels | Zustand or composition |
| Custom UI components | shadcn/ui primitives first |
| Snapshot tests | Behaviour-based RTL tests |
| `<BrowserRouter>` JSX tree | `createBrowserRouter` data router |
| `window.location` for navigation | `useNavigate` |
| Per-page auth checks | Layout-level `AuthGuard` |
